('Dominic Egger (MBA - Glion)', 'Dominic', 'Egger (MBA - Glion)', 'Director of Operations Thailand Wyndham Destinations / Travel + Leisure Co', 'https://www.linkedin.com/in/dominic-egger-mba-glion-85ab298', 'dominic-egger-mba-glion-85ab298', $${"about": "Passionate in hospitality.  Driven and engaged leader to bring success to your business. Obsessed with the customer experience and journey. Building empowered and engaged teams. Financial success with long term strategy and social responsibility in the neighborhood. \n\nI held various leadership roles in Europe, Asia, Africa and Australia with opening, refurbishments and reorganization of hotels. From 450 room corporate Swissôtel Beijing, to a private 15 villa luxury boutique Fregate island resort in the Seychelles. High end corporate hotel Stamford Plaza Brisbane with multiple Food & Beverage outlets to the world renowned leading hotel of the world Palace Hotel Gstaad. \n\nStarted in 2008 with IHG at the Holiday Inn Brisbane. Supported multiple hotels in the region in need periods as Acting General Manager for refurbishments and re-brand. Finished in 2012 in Brisbane as Hotel Manager reporting directly to the Director of Operations Australia and leading the refurbishment of Holiday Inn Brisbane. Reaching top 3 in guest recognition of all Holiday Inn properties in Australasia. Recipient of the General Manager Leadership Awards for 2010 and 2011. \n\nMoved in 2012 to Thailand to open the first Holiday Inn Express in a beach resort location. Within a short pre-opening time frame of 4 month, setting up the hotel for a successful journey. My support was given to all the other HIE hotel openings in South East Asia. 2014 Area General Manager for all the 4 Thailand Holiday Inn Express hotels before they have been integrated into the SEA IHG Hotels. Awarded General Manager of the Year in AMEA. Q3 Frontrunner award 2014 & 3 HR awards in 2014. In 2015 moved to Holiday Inn Resort Penang in Malaysia and within the first year have been recognized internally from IHG and externally on TripAdvisor for the fantastic increase in Guest Service Recognition. Moved on TripAdvisor from rank 8 to 3rd place. \n\nEnd of 2017 back to Phuket and opening the first Wyndham Grand in South East Asia. Unique hotel with 150 Suites and Villas with individual private pools. Trend setting F&B concepts for outlets and driving special experiences with floating breakfast. several awards and accolades moved the property into the top ten on TripAdvisor. Driven innovation and being well ahead in todays guest experience and communication. Run two years 90% occupancy in 2018 & 2019. Post mandated covid closure, now continuously increasing the occupancy month over month. Supported and trained the Indonesian and Phuket hotels in financial Budget process in 2019 & 2020.", "addressCountryOnly": "Thailand", "addressWithCountry": "Phuket, Thailand", "addressWithoutCountry": "Phuket", "backgroundPic": "https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/C4E16AQEwA7we03eH6w/profile-displaybackgroundimage-shrink_350_1400/profile-displaybackgroundimage-shrink_350_1400/0/1517747176238?e=1778112000&v=beta&t=KNg8BnB30aw0GWDNmmnouDkVRDSFE2ZytT4dfOemGCA", "companyIndustry": "Hospitality", "companyLinkedin": "https://www.linkedin.com/company/wyndham-destinations/", "companyName": "Wyndham Destinations", "companySize": "10001-0", "companyWebsite": "https://www.linkedin.com/company/travelleisureco/", "connections": "8354", "creatorWebsite/0/category": "COMPANY", "creatorWebsite/0/url": "wyndhamgrandphuket.com", "currentJobDuration": "3 yrs 3 mos", "currentJobDurationInYrs": "3.25", "educations/0/companyId": "42091", "educations/0/companyLink1": "https://www.linkedin.com/school/glion-institute-of-higher-education/", "educations/0/companyUrn": "urn:li:fsd_company:42091", "educations/0/description": "Completed Course Subjects: \n- Success Strategies for the Hospitality and Service Industries \n- Managing Service Operations in the Evolving Business Environ