https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/D5603AQHq0KldtRdOVQ/profile-displayphoto-shrink_800_800/B56ZdfUkhtGoAc-/0/1749650922327?e=1778112000&v=beta&t=cuXuTJv0ODfiqJ1osPiO_Himbc56hokX2eICULPRzAg", "peopleAlsoViewed/24/public_identifier": "levent-bilgir-b4301a48", "peopleAlsoViewed/24/url": "https://linkedin.com/in/ACoAAAn4GuMBhqAMTVMWjmVl4oCtxLI0enmyF7Y", "peopleAlsoViewed/25/entity_urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAF6xuABcwWud2lBON0bggVSXuXfK6wQavQ", "peopleAlsoViewed/25/first_name": "Jean-matthieu", "peopleAlsoViewed/25/follower_count": "5537", "peopleAlsoViewed/25/headline": "General Manager | Luxury & Lifestyle Hotels | Pre-Opening, Rebranding & Operational Excellence | Driving Profitability, Guest Experience & Owner Value across Southeast Asia", "peopleAlsoViewed/25/last_name": "Beroujon", "peopleAlsoViewed/25/premium": "false", "peopleAlsoViewed/25/profile_picture": "https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/D4E03AQHAOFQ51VtWgA/profile-displayphoto-crop_800_800/B4EZowiWgCGYAI-/0/1761750903694?e=1778112000&v=beta&t=RIRtz-8lqkcgFfFT5N88RPFhkn6EbOYb7xI2WdQFAoU", "peopleAlsoViewed/25/public_identifier": "jmberoujon", "peopleAlsoViewed/25/url": "https://linkedin.com/in/ACoAAAF6xuABcwWud2lBON0bggVSXuXfK6wQavQ", "profilePic": "https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/C4E03AQEsXKxWweM-SQ/profile-displayphoto-shrink_400_400/profile-displayphoto-shrink_400_400/0/1517747175492?e=1778112000&v=beta&t=RkIQfGdtEKN7dhQdYoLY0AdBlQg4PErT2r3boFL4MlA", "profilePicHighQuality": "https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/C4E03AQEsXKxWweM-SQ/profile-displayphoto-shrink_400_400/profile-displayphoto-shrink_400_400/0/1517747175492?e=1778112000&v=beta&t=RkIQfGdtEKN7dhQdYoLY0AdBlQg4PErT2r3boFL4MlA", "publicIdentifier": "dominic-egger-mba-glion-85ab298", "recommendations/0/context": "Dominic worked with Michael but they were at different companies", "recommendations/0/date": "July 9, 2025", "recommendations/0/description": "I've had the privilege of crossing paths with many professionals in global hospitality, but few stand out like Michael Massey. Michael is not just a voice in wellness and sustainable tourism—he’s a force. A clear, credible leader who speaks truth where others lean on trends and tokenism.\n\nWith deep roots in wellness tourism, Michael has the rare ability to craft strategies that are both holistically enriching and commercially viable. He understands that true wellbeing isn’t something you slap on a brochure—it’s built into the fabric of guest experience, operations, and community engagement.\n\nIn the realm of sustainability, Michael doesn’t settle for surface-level certifications. He champions initiatives with integrity, accountability, and long-term impact—the kind of leadership Asia’s tourism sector urgently needs right now.\n\nAnd when it comes to public speaking, Michael delivers. Whether in front of government bodies, industry panels, or grassroots forums, he communicates with clarity, conviction, and purpose. He doesn’t sugarcoat. He challenges. He inspires.\n\nIf you’re looking for someone to drive meaningful, measurable change in wellness and sustainable tourism, Michael Massey is the real deal.", "recommendations/0/name": "Michael Massey", "recommendations/0/subtitle": "Student at the University of Life | Health | Motorcycles | Dogs | Curiosity", "recommendations/0/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/masseymichael/", "recommendations/0/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAL-iSoBlvFK1kQcpKuGEONngxhlJgDRLhs", "recommendations/1/context": "Dominic worked with Marta on the same team", "recommendations/1/date": "April 3, 2024", "recommendations/1/description": "I am delighted to provide a glowing recommendation for Marta Grutka, who I had the pleasure of working closely with during her tenure as the Corporate PR Director at Wyndham Destinations (now Travel + Leisure Co.), in my capacity as Director of Operations WD Thailand. Marta's exceptional comms skills and commitment to excellence consistently impressed me throughout our professional partnership, and her ability to deliver results while fostering a collaborative and inclusive work environment make her an invaluable asset to any organization. \n\nMarta possesses an unparalleled ability to leverage her extensive network and connections within the industry to drive impactful brand and business outcomes. This, along with her strategic approach and forward planning, were instrumental in getting influential reporters from various publications to visit our Wyndham Hotels and Resorts across Thailand, resulting in positive stories that showcased our offerings and values - including our commitment to ESG initiatives - to new audiences. \n\nIn addition to her exemplary PR prowess, Marta demonstrated a genuine commitment to supporting and empowering our resort team members. Whether conducting “PR 101 media training,” or overseeing the nomination process for female team members for the inaugural IWTA awards, her dedication to promoting diversity, inclusion, and empowering talent was clear.\n\nIn conclusion, I wholeheartedly recommend Marta Grutka for any role that requires top-notch PR expertise, strategic leadership, and a passion for driving positive change. She is undoubtedly a standout professional in her field, and I am confident that she will continue to excel in all her endeavours.", "recommendations/1/name": "Marta Grutka ", "recommendations/1/subtitle": "Chief of Staff | Corporate Affairs | Commercial Leader | 10x ROI • $30MM+ P&L • APAC • EMEA • U.S.", "recommendations/1/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/martagrutka/", "recommendations/1/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAAYkvIBZbAWZMWYfZB1Ij5E78bW_MnFxP8", "recommendations/2/context": "Dominic worked with Arles but they were at different companies", "recommendations/2/date": "July 16, 2023", "recommendations/2/description": "I am writing to wholeheartedly recommend Arles Sanchez for his exceptional expertise in marketing campaigns and influencer support within the hospitality industry. I had the pleasure of collaborating with Arles during my tenure as the General Manager at Wyndham Grand Phuket, and his contributions were invaluable to our success.\n\nArles possesses a deep understanding of the hotel & resort market, and his strategic approach to marketing campaigns played a pivotal role in attracting guests and boosting our brand visibility. His ability to identify target audiences, develop compelling messaging, and implement innovative marketing strategies consistently exceeded expectations. Arles' dedication and attention to detail ensured that our campaigns were well-executed and aligned with our brand values.\n\nFurthermore, Arles's proficiency in leveraging international influencers was instrumental in expanding our reach and attracting a diverse audience. His knowledge of the influencer landscape, coupled with his excellent communication skills, allowed us to establish meaningful collaborations with influential personalities who aligned perfectly with our brand. Arles ensured that each partnership was mutually beneficial, resulting in increased brand awareness and engagement.\n\nI have no doubt that Arles's passion for his work, coupled with his strategic mindset and professionalism, will continue to bring immense value to any organization he collaborates with. His ability to adapt to new challenges and stay updated with industry trends is commendable, making him a valuable asset for any marketing team.", "recommendations/2/name": "Arles Sanchez", "recommendations/2/subtitle": "Full-Funnel Marketing Strategist | Brand Management & Strategic Communications Expert | Creative & Data-Driven Innovator | Passionate About Cultivating Brand Loyalty & Delivering Impactful Content", "recommendations/2/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/arles-sanchez-2618a2124/", "recommendations/2/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAB6-WOkBbbYL6IEqIVuqy7qQH4an6kSlNQo", "recommendations/3/context": "Dominic was Felix Hug .. 's client", "recommendations/3/date": "September 28, 2022", "recommendations/3/description": "Worked with Felix in two projects for international resort photography and both times the outcome has been amazing. Professional preparation and communication in advance to ensure a perfect outcome. A picture paints a thousand words and in both resorts with different target market Eye On Asia hit it perfectly. Mood shots to trigger emotions...", "recommendations/3/name": "Felix Hug ..  Eyes on Asia", "recommendations/3/subtitle": "Hospitality Industry Photography", "recommendations/3/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/felix-hug-eyes-on-asia-91697513/", "recommendations/3/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAALP-eIBDnMZK-4H-PWNlSa7qm2a69veqKg", "recommendations/4/context": "Dominic was Renny's client", "recommendations/4/date": "March 5, 2021", "recommendations/4/description": "Working with Renny was insightful and great value for myself and our resort. Renny looked in her role as regional revenue & distribution manager after our first Wyndham Grand in South East Asia and with her support, maximised outstanding results balancing the fine act of occupancy and adr through all seasons. The resort under the revenue guidance of Renny has achieved 2 years in a row 90% occupancy full and a 1st ranking in RGI. Renny was our sounding board for ideas and new strategies, advisor and analyst for our performance and always there if there was a connectivity issue or challenge.\n\nHer consultive approach made our resort team comfortable to work with and reach out and driven the productivity. Always driving new creative ideas and fresh opportunities in the market, specific to our unique resort. \nWhilst we have worked in different countries, Renny had a focus and understanding of Thailand market, seasonality and competitor set. Always listen to our team and enhanced the discussion with valuable insights. \n\nI personally appreciate the trust and open communication we had. Able to “agree to disagree” on certain topics and professionally drive this forward to increase our business successfully ahead.", "recommendations/4/name": "Renny Limanhadi", "recommendations/4/subtitle": "Revenue Growth | Regional Sales, Marketing, and Customer", "recommendations/4/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/rennylimanhadi/", "recommendations/4/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAecHvABAqbPVUMa9ivBpGSc99oDGd20loY", "recommendations/5/context": "Dominic worked with Bruce but they were at different companies", "recommendations/5/date": "January 8, 2021", "recommendations/5/description": "I am currently working alongside Bruce, in my capacity as General Manager of the Wyndham Grand Phuket Kalim Bay while he is the General Manager at a sister property, Wyndham Sea Pearl Resort Phuket. \n  \nI have experienced a very positive working relationship with Bruce as we support each other and share resources, ideas, and strategies.  It is fantastic to have a trusted sounding board to review processes, plans, and new initiatives.  Our open exchange of knowledge and information has been especially beneficial during COVID -19 as we maneuvered through the government-mandated closure of our resorts and the safe re-openings.  \n  \nBruce arrived nearly two years ago and took over a challenging and financially struggling resort. He efficiently turned the property around before the onset of COVID -19, increasing occupancy, and guest satisfaction. He is team focused and a passionate trainer and educator. Leading by example and present within the resort showing his genuine hospitality from the heart. \n  \nI continue to appreciate his support and enjoy working together.   \n", "recommendations/5/name": "Bruce Dupuis", "recommendations/5/subtitle": "Regional Director of Operations, Cogir Senior Living", "recommendations/5/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/bruce-dupuis-55772919/", "recommendations/5/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAPYRdMBuLkjEk4zzN0V463aIRb7Tji5cgs", "recommendations/6/context": "Dominic worked with Cookie on the same team", "recommendations/6/date": "October 26, 2018", "recommendations/6/description": "Where to start!!! Khun Cookie has been an amazing support to me and our team. We have been the start up in setting up the hotel brand across South East Asia and Khun Cookie was the Personal Assistant to the head of Holiday Inn Express and Shared Service Office. Making sure that everyone was on track, did not miss deadlines, supported where required and organized continuously the next steps. Arranged meetings in Bangkok, Singapore, Jakarta and was always a step ahead to surprise the teams. Long days for her with getting everyone organized, set up and arranged but managed those events really well. Always great choices fitting the respective group. A good heart and passionate in what she does and this comes continuously across in all her work.", "recommendations/6/name": "Cookie K.", "recommendations/6/subtitle": "Executive Assistant to Leadership | Business Development & Client Relations | Driving Project Success in Hospitality & Real Estate", "recommendations/6/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/kanjanattee/", "recommendations/6/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAPbieEBO2yeUCOx_cGwDC5aT-tsLJlk3oM", "recommendations/7/context": "Dominic was Daniel Tan WJ's client", "recommendations/7/date": "October 7, 2018", "recommendations/7/description": "We have been super pleased with the dedication, interactions and support Daniel has extended to our team to make a successful launch of the HandiGo App for our hotel. Whilst introducing new items to a business are often a challenge, he managed the project very well and included all the key stakeholders on multiple sessions as a group and individual. He removed the fear factor in the department Managers explained the ease and benefit for their teams. Additional he continuously follow up for not only support but as well for guest interactions, which has been amazing. Very pleased with the outcome of the set up for our hotel which the success lies all from Daniel's dedication pre and post set up.. Not expected to that level of 24x7 drive but amazed and very pleased. \nThank you \nDominic", "recommendations/7/name": "Daniel Tan WJ Kit Chaiyaped", "recommendations/7/subtitle": "Be Confident, Be Positive & Never Give up, till you Achieve the Goals you Set!", "recommendations/7/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/dtwjkit85/", "recommendations/7/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAABvnEjIBOkitGMhIgEcaelxpxiNIC_YuOj0", "recommendations/8/context": "Dominic worked with Jonathan but on different teams", "recommendations/8/date": "September 11, 2018", "recommendations/8/description": "I was pleased to work for Jonathan Mills from 2012 to 2014 as our head of Operation Holiday Inn Express South East Asia and IHG Shared Service Offices. Setting up the success driven culture and the legacy of the Holiday Inn Express spirit in South East Asia was to his full credit with his persistent dedication to the long term goal and rapid growth of the portfolio.\n\nHis passionate, engaging and genuine approach made me and our leadership team driven to deliver and succeed as a team and not just a single unit. Jonathan enabled support between different properties to cross share the learnings and was a key in the owner and operations team relationships. It was an absolute pleasure to work for him and would never hesitate in the future if an opening would arise to work again under his brilliant leadership.\n", "recommendations/8/name": "Jonathan Mills", "recommendations/8/subtitle": "Hotel Group Director / MD / CEO / COO🔸Hotel & Hospitality Portfolio Management ✯ Brand Development ✯ New Market Entry ✯ Sustainable Growth ✯ ESG ✯ Digitization ✯ Operations Management ✯ Franchising", "recommendations/8/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/jonathan-mills-hospitality-executive/", "recommendations/8/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAYRgTYBy0ahH-Jt-Vzf9zJX1fCKDOoCe2w", "recommendations/9/context": "Wendy was Dominic's client", "recommendations/9/date": "July 17, 2017", "recommendations/9/description": "Wendy has helped our hotel to review, update and train our risk assessment profiles and crisis management response plan. This was a challenging task, working with the local labor force, coach, understand and then re-write the SOP flow charts and processes for all team levels to understand. From entry level employee's to emergency response team and crisis management team for a safe hotel operation. Her input was fantastic and enabled to make it easy to understand and be effective in crisis situations. ", "recommendations/9/name": "Wendy Bailey", "recommendations/9/subtitle": "Principal Risk & Safety Leader | Major Projects & Fatal Risk | Enterprise Risk, Critical Controls & Assurance", "recommendations/9/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/wendybaile/", "recommendations/9/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAGwgBMB8N96z-gBIDav_akihkU5olXEbWs", "recommendations/10/context": "Dominic worked with Tracy on the same team", "recommendations/10/date": "July 11, 2008", "recommendations/10/description": "Tracy is a first class operator.  She is multi-skilled and always achieves outstanding results through her work, whether it is in public relations, marketing or event management.  She has a natural flair for business and an impressive ability to conceptualise and stage events.  Tracy’s ability to secure and manage major sponsors is commendable.  She was embraced quickly and openly by all in the Stamford team, from the most senior to the most junior, and remains a good friend today.", "recommendations/10/name": "Tracy Johnston", "recommendations/10/subtitle": "Freelance Brand Writer & Strategist", "recommendations/10/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/tracy-johnston-2b90b49/", "recommendations/10/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAGdp60BVe-EjFtllBfkH7n793fgQqe_nd4", "recommendationsReceived/0/context": "Rohan was Dominic's client", "recommendationsReceived/0/date": "April 22, 2024", "recommendationsReceived/0/description": "Dominic's expertise in hotel management and hospitality technology has been invaluable to Techie Stays.\n\nHe consulted with our team on honing our AI content solution. \n\nI look forward to working with him on our next project.", "recommendationsReceived/0/name": "Rohan Watt", "recommendationsReceived/0/subtitle": "I help hotels answer guest questions instantly - in any language - using Voice AI and AI review responses.", "recommendationsReceived/0/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/rohan-watt-56264430/", "recommendationsReceived/0/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAaAahoBF5un_OWpWqXtumADRCaDq_sox7o", "recommendationsReceived/1/context": "Tracy worked with Dominic on the same team", "recommendationsReceived/1/date": "July 12, 2008", "recommendationsReceived/1/description": "Dominic is one of the most organised and financially adept individuals I have had the pleasure to work with.  His project management skills are outstanding and were instrumental in successfully managing a large and multi-faceted operation. Dominic transitions seamlessly between strategic and operational demands - always in a calm and decisive manner. I always felt honoured to have someone with Dominic's level of expertise and international experience on board as part of our executive team.", "recommendationsReceived/1/name": "Tracy Johnston", "recommendationsReceived/1/subtitle": "Freelance Brand Writer & Strategist", "recommendationsReceived/1/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/tracy-johnston-2b90b49/", "recommendationsReceived/1/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAGdp60BVe-EjFtllBfkH7n793fgQqe_nd4", "skills/0/title": "Pre-opening", "skills/1/title": "Rooms Division", "skills/2/title": "Hotels", "skills/3/title": "Resorts", "skills/4/title": "Banquets", "skills/5/title": "Hospitality", "skills/6/title": "Front Office", "skills/7/title": "Food & Beverage", "skills/8/title": "Hotel Management", "skills/9/title": "Yield Management", "skills/10/title": "Revenue Analysis", "skills/11/title": "Hospitality Management", "skills/12/title": "Hospitality Industry", "ski